# jet-pi-troubleshooter - Overview (L1)

## Triggers
- "investigate PI-XXXXX", "troubleshoot this PI", "what caused this outage"
- "find the root cause", "what changed", "why is X service down"
- Any request to correlate changes with production failures
- NOT for: pi timeline, pi catchup, pi post-mortem, pi prodmeet (use jet-pi-summary)

## Evidence Streams
1. Jira ticket data (timeline, components, comments)
2. Datadog observability (error logs, metrics spikes, events)
3. GitHub PR history (infra and app changes)
4. AWS events (CloudTrail, CloudWatch, Route53)
5. Wiz security (vulnerabilities, misconfigurations)

## Dependencies
- jet-company-standards (acli, gh)
- jet-datadog (pup)
- jet-aws (AWS CLI)
- wiz-skill (Wiz API)

## Self-Improving
- Check `examples/` for past PI investigations with similar symptoms
- Apply patterns from `learnings.md` before starting fresh analysis
- After each investigation, add a new example and update learnings
